40|$|Militant <b>{{democracy}}</b> <b>is</b> {{an attempt}} to defend democracy against totalitarian parties that would use democratic procedures to rise to power. This article {{is focused on the}} consistency of the concept of 'militant democracy'. I argue that what militant <b>democracy</b> defends <b>is</b> not the democratic procedure itself but rather certain rights and the rule of law, and that those elements may in fact <b>be</b> compromised by <b>democracy.</b> This applies both if the democratic procedure is concerned and if <b>democracy</b> <b>is</b> interpreted as a reflection of the will of the people. Those elements may <b>be</b> upheld, but <b>democracy</b> <b>is</b> to be mitigated rather than fortified in order to do so...|$|R
